Job description 1 : 
Job Summary:
Manages all aspects of indirect tax compliance (GST, VAT, excise duty). Ensures filings are accurate, reconciled, and compliant with evolving regulations.
Responsibilities:
Prepare and file GST/VAT/excise returns in India and applicable jurisdictions.
Reconcile input credits and output liabilities; identify mismatches and root causes.
Monitor regulatory changes; assess impact and implement changes.
Respond to notices; coordinate with tax authorities; assist during audits.

Qualifications:
Bachelor’s in Commerce/Finance; CA/ICWA/CPA preferred.
3–5 years in indirect tax compliance within a corporate environment.

Skills & Competencies:
Strong knowledge of GST, VAT, excise duty.
Expertise in Tally, ClearTax, SAP FICO; advanced MS Excel proficiency.
Analytical problem-solving, attention to detail, stakeholder communication.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 2 : 
Handles corporate income tax across jurisdictions, ensuring timely filing, tax provisioning, and alignment with statutory requirements.
Responsibilities:
Prepare and review quarterly/annual tax provisions (for example, under ASC 740 or Indian Accounting Standards).
Manage computation and filing of corporate tax returns.
Liaise with auditors; maintain technical working papers.
Review deferred tax, permanent differences, and deferred tax assets/liabilities.

Qualifications:
CA/CPA; 4–6 years in corporate tax within multinational corporations.
Experience with international taxation and DTAA application.
